<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="27" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,374,940]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,517,662,688]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
The species has distribution in South America, among secondary vegetation (
<bibRefCitation author="Lima, J. R. &amp; Mansano, V. F." pageId="10" pageNumber="27" pagination="564 - 613" refId="ref17012" refString="Lima, J. R. &amp; Mansano, V. F. (2011) A familia Leguminosae na Serra de Baturite, Ceara, uma area de Floresta Atlantica no semiarido brasileiro. Rodriguesia 62: 564 - 613. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860201162309" type="journal article" year="2011">Lima &amp; Mansano2011</bibRefCitation>
).In 
<collectingCountry box="[344,415,698,724]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is present in the Central-West,Northeast, Southeast and South regions in the phytogeographic domains of Caatinga, Cerrado, Atlantic Rainforest and Pantanal, in rocky fields, seasonal semideciduous forest, rain forest and in sandbank areas (INCT - Virtual Herbarium of Flora and Fungi). This species occurs preferably in the undergrowth of the forest (
<bibRefCitation author="Queiroz, R. T." box="[435,594,806,832]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" refId="ref18260" refString="Queiroz, R. T. (2021) Fabaceae do Cariri paraibano. Nova Xavantina, 630 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.46420 / 9786588319604" type="book" year="2021">Queiroz 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,374,940]" box="[189,663,842,869]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,842,868]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Found with flowers in May.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,374,940]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brandegee" authorityYear="1905" baseAuthorityName="Humboldt &amp; Bonpland ex Willdenow" baseAuthorityYear="1809" box="[189,451,879,905]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Centrosema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittatum">
<emphasis box="[189,451,879,905]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Centrosema sagittatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily recognized, mainly, by the vine habit, 1–3 foliolate imparipinnate leaves, opposite, sagittate leaflets, dialypetalous corolla, papilionaceous, whitish and reniform seeds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
